## 3. The Union of Free Systems (UFS)

### Structure & civic life
- **Citizenship must be earned through service.** Two civic tiers: **Citizens** (full political rights) and **Residents** (comfortable, prosperous, disenfranchised).
- Clean institutional language: directorates, acronyms, plain words.
- Capital world: **New Geneva** — an idealistic founding name, now the seat of a war bureaucracy. (The Imperium refuses the name in official documents, using its old Concord-era catalog designation instead.)

### Daily life
A prosperous consumer society funding a distant war. Most citizens have never seen the Reach: war bonds, patriotic media, liberation documentaries, veterans who come home strange.

### Ideology & view of the Imperium
A **moral crusade — "liberate the serfs."** Sincere for true believers, abstract for everyone else. Core hypocrisy: crusading against hereditary caste while running an earned-citizenship two-tier society. ("You have castes too. You just call them Residents.") Liberation also happens to be expansion — every freed world becomes UFS territory.

### Military
- **FLEETCOM** (Fleet Command) and **UGF** (Union Ground Forces).
- Tech superiority: drones, orbital fire discipline, combined-arms doctrine.
- Every casualty is a voter, a family, a news story. Expensive soldiers, careful doctrine.
- Standing temptation as the war grinds: autonomous weapons, or even a cloning program of their own — what the war does to the Union's soul is a core theme.

